#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:49
msgid "Reporting Bugs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:52
msgid "Before Submitting a Bug Report"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:54
msgid ""
"A good bug report shouldn't leave others needing to chase you up for more "
"information. Therefore, we ask you to investigate carefully, collect "
"information and describe the issue in detail in your report."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:57
msgid ""
"Please complete the following steps in advance to help us fix any potential "
"bug as fast as possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:59
msgid "Make sure that you are using the latest version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:60
msgid "Ensure that the issue can be reliably reproduced."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:61
msgid "Collect information about the bug:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:63
msgid "Stack traces"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:64
msgid "Sphinx log for the build"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:65
msgid "Sphinx configuration and usage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:66
msgid "Python, Rust and Sphinx versions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:67
msgid "OS, Platform and Version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:69
msgid ""
"We use GitLab issues to track bugs and errors. If you run into an issue with "
"the project:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:71
msgid ""
"`Open an Issue <https://gitlab.com/munir0b0t/sphinxcontrib-rust/issues/"
"new>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:72
msgid "Explain the behavior you would expect and the actual behavior."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:73
msgid ""
"Please provide as much context as possible and describe the *reproduction "
"steps* that someone else can follow to recreate the issue on their own. This "
"usually includes your code. For good bug reports you should isolate the "
"problem and create a reduced test case."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:76
msgid "Provide the information you collected in the previous section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:78
msgid "Once it's filed:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:80
msgid "The project team will label the issue accordingly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:81
msgid "A team member will try to reproduce the issue with your provided steps."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:83
msgid ""
"If there are no reproduction steps or no obvious way to reproduce the issue, "
"the team will ask you for those steps and mark the issue as ``needs-repro``. "
"Bugs with the ``needs-repro`` tag will not be addressed until they are "
"reproduced."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:87
msgid ""
"If the team is able to reproduce the issue, it will be marked ``needs-fix``, "
"as well as possibly other tags (such as ``critical``), and the issue will be "
"prioritized for addressing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:89
msgid ""
"If you have a potential fix for the issue, please also `open a MR <https://"
"gitlab.com/munir0b0t/sphinxcontrib-rust/-/merge_requests/new>`_ referencing "
"the issue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:93
msgid "Suggesting Enhancements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:95
msgid ""
"This section guides you through submitting an enhancement suggestion for "
"sphinxcontrib-rust, **including completely new features and minor "
"improvements to existing functionality**. Following these guidelines will "
"help maintainers and the community to understand your suggestion and find "
"related suggestions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:100
msgid "Before Submitting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:102
msgid ""
"Check the `Gitlab issues`_ for any open issues that might cover the "
"situtation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:105
msgid "Submitting suggestions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:107
msgid "Enhancement suggestions are tracked as `GitLab issues`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:109
msgid ""
"Use a **clear and descriptive title** for the issue to identify the "
"suggestion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:110
msgid ""
"Provide a **step-by-step description of the suggested enhancement** in as "
"many details as possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:111
msgid ""
"**Describe the current behavior** and **explain which behavior you expected "
"to see instead** and why. At this point you can also tell which alternatives "
"do not work for you."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:113
msgid ""
"You may want to **include screenshots or expected output** which help you "
"demonstrate the steps or point out the part which the suggestion is related "
"to."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:115
msgid ""
"**Explain why this enhancement would be useful** to most sphinxcontrib-rust "
"users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:120
msgid "Styleguides"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:123
msgid "Rust"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:125
msgid ""
"A ``rustfmt.toml`` file is included with project for the Rust code style. "
"Make sure to execute ``cargo +nightly fmt`` before submitting the MR. The CI "
"will verify the code style and fail if it does not conform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:128
msgid ""
"The CI will also run ``cargo +nightly clippy`` on the Rust crate and expect "
"a success return code from it. Please address any new issues detected by "
"clippy, even if the CI passes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:132
msgid "Python"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:134
msgid ""
"The project uses `black <https://github.com/psf/black>`_ for formating the "
"Python code. Make sure to run ``black .`` before submitting the MR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:137
msgid ""
"The CI will also run ``pylint`` on the code. The ``.pylintrc`` to use is "
"included in the project repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:140
msgid "Commit Messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:142
msgid ""
"Please create meaningful commit messages in the MR. You will be asked to "
"edit the commit message if the maintainers feel so. The general format of "
"the commit message should be ::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:145
msgid ""
"Brief description of the MR's goals\n"
"\n"
"A detailed description of the why and how of the changes\n"
"in the MR. This can be as long as you like.\n"
"\n"
"closes #<issue>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:154
msgid "Join The Project Team"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:156
msgid "The project requires a good understanding of Sphinx and how it works."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../CONTRIBUTING.rst:158
msgid ""
"It also uses both Rust and Python, so you must be able to review other "
"people's code in both languages. Familiarize yourself with the project's "
"organization and developer notes using :doc:`docs/developing`."
msgstr ""

